description: Commuters are being urged to check their journey details before they set off.
title: London to Norwich trains disrupted due to fallen tree
title_page: London to Norwich trains disrupted due to fallen tree - BBC News
maintext:
Trains were cancelled and delayed after a tree fell on overhead electric wires.
Network Rail said there was major disruption on Greater Anglia lines after the incident was reported at 09:08 GMT.
Services were disrupted between London Liverpool Street and Norwich, Harwich Town, Walton-on-the-Naze, Colchester Town, Braintree and Clacton-on-Sea.
A spokesperson said disruption was expected until 12:00.
